\n<Old Man>Ah yes, of course! Sorry, my memory is not what it once was.
Please, take this as an apology.
\n<Old Man>Oh... silly me. Well it's nice to meet you!
\n<Shopkeeper>Ah, you customer, yes? Here to buy, buy, buy? Yes! Of course you are...
\n<Old Lady>Oh! You startled me! What can I do for you, young lady?
\n<Old Lady>Ah... I am sorry I can only spare 5, but it's yours!
\n<Old Lady>Well of course! I baked this earlier today, take it!
\n<Old Lady>Will this be ok? I prepared it just for you!
\n<Old Lady>Well then, it was nice to meet you. Have a good day!
\n<Old Lady>Hello again, I hope you're having a good day!
\n<Stall Owner>Damn it! If my wife keeps giving things away for free, she's gonna put me out of business... But nonetheless, I have things for sale. You buying something?
\n<Schoolgirl>Arggh! I hate the buses here, they seem to arrive constantly, but it's never the one I want! I am gonna be so late...
